According to statistics, 30-75% of people who have been arrested because of the drunk driving are back in the car.
This would be prevented by Alcolock, as the system connected to the vehicle establishes the alcohol content of the air infused. If it is higher than permitted, or if the driver did not blow into the device at all, the system will not allow the car to be launched.
The cost of an instrument of more than 1000 euros would cost the offender.
A 2007 study in the USA showed that vehicles equipped with such instruments could reduce the number of infringements by up to 65% in the first year after installation.
In Spain, it is estimated that this rule could save 115 people every year.
The measure focuses on infringements for two reasons: on the one hand, it is easier to prevent them from becoming a criminal offence,
On the other hand, it is easier to introduce, as the implementation of the legal reform takes place in the usual field, while the necessary criminal reform would require a basic amendment.
The instrument is not yet available in any commercial form in the Spanish market, although it has already been installed in some industrial and public service vehicles in experimental mode.
