It has been two years since, and more and more companies have been taking a bow to marine energy, including those who have been committed to traditional energy.
“Chevron studies the technologies that utilize the energy of the oceans and considers the possibility of cooperation with us,” said a spokesman for an American oil giant, Wall Street Journal’s economic newspaper.
The cooperation in question concerns the acquisition of the authorisation necessary for the launch of the Alaskan project for the exploitation of marine energy issued by the U.S. Energy Committee.
This is not a small matter, especially if we consider the US to continue oil extraction in Alaska, and even President Bush has recently launched a plan for further drilling.
In addition to Chevron, Verdant Power Inc. and Ocean Power in New Jersey also walks the way of energy coming out of the sea. The amounts invested so far, as you can know about the details, are proving a growing interest.
Technology is expected to be developed.
According to experts, it is still a matter of initial technology, even because the energy obtained from the sea does not disperse doubts about the environmental impact.
The existing facilities like Portugal or Scotland are both small and therefore do not cause too much problems with ecosystem.
However, in order to produce energy in greater scales, it is necessary to have facilities that have a more significant environmental impact.
There are several options: Ocean Power uses, for example, a interconnected bonus system.
The waves and the shocks moving the bonuses are transformed into hydraulic pressure by the plugs and cylinders placed inside them.
The pressure is turning a turbine, and it feeds a generator.
The power of electricity comes from cables under the sea to land.
At the same time, there are four similar facilities in the planning phase, which are already waiting for a federal permit. Some of the energy produced would be used in a military facility.
On the other hand, Verdant Power has already launched energy production for a shopping mall and a parking lot using the six submarine turbines located in East River in New York.
At the time of flooding, the movement of water turns the tiles of turbines, and this circulation nourishes the generator.
Verdant said that he had a long list of partners waiting for permits only for the use of energy.
After the rollers, the current.
Currently, different attention needs to be paid to the possibilities that can be exploited through the current flow.
Although it is a temporary phenomenon, the current is more predictable than the wind, the sun, or the waves, it is therefore considered to be a more reliable source of energy.
New York, Maine and Alaska and other coastal states spent $7.5 million in 2008, just to extract the energy supplied by the flood. This amount is expected to increase to 35 million in 2009.
